body:
Probably not a serious problem, as no real system could ever actually have a bus this wide, but the following module causes an assertion failure:

```
module test (q);
	parameter MEMSIZE = 1 << 16;
	output [MEMSIZE-1:0] q;

	reg [MEMSIZE-1:0] q_buf;
	reg output_enable;

	assign q = output_enable ? q_buf : 1'bz;
endmodule
```

Attempting to compile this causes the following error:

> This application has requested the Runtime to terminate it in an unusual way.
> Please contact the application's support team for more information.
> Assertion failed!
> 
> Program: C:\software\iverilog\lib\ivl\ivl.exe
> File: ../verilog-10.1.1/libmisc/StringHeap.cc, Line 48
> 
> Expression: (len+1) <= HEAPCELL
>

